 FORMER Chief of Army Staff Gen. T. Y. Danjuma has donated N60 million  for the renovation of Government College, Katsina-Ala in Benue Northeast Senatorial District. Danjuma is an old student of the college. The National President of Katsina-Ala Old Boys Association (KAOBA), Mr.  Harouna Adamu, disclosed this yesterday when he visited Governor Samuel Ortom at the Government  House, Makurdi. He said KAOBA members came to seek Ortom’s approval to begin renovation of the school.  Ortom hailed Danjuma for the donation. He assured KAOBA members of his support for the renovation of their alma mater.